{"questionId":"15718","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A potter sells <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> vases per month.</p>\n<p>His monthly profit in Australian dollars (AUD) can be modelled by</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage mjpage__block\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\" alttext=\"P\\left( x \\right) =&nbsp; - \\frac{1}{5}{x^3} + 7{x^2} - 120{\\text{,}}\\,\\,x \\geqslant 0.\">\n  <mi>P</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>7</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>120</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>⩾</mo>\n  <mn>0.</mn>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"P\">\n  <mi>P</mi>\n</math></span> if no vases are sold.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p>−120 (AUD)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)&nbsp; &nbsp;(C1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15718","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.T_15a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of P if no vases are sold.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differe